---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Date Calculator — How Many Days Between Dates | Clockr"
	description="Calculate the exact number of days, weeks, months and years between any two dates. Free online date calculator."
>
	<div class="date-page">
		<!-- PAGE HEADER -->
		<div class="date-header">
			<div class="date-eyebrow">📅 Dates & Duration</div>
			<h1 class="date-title">
				<span class="date-gradient">Date</span><br />
				<span class="date-gradient">Calculator</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="date-subtitle">
				Find out exactly how long between any two dates
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- INPUT CARD -->
		<div class="date-form-card">
			<div class="date-inputs">
				<div class="date-input-wrap">
					<label class="date-label" for="start-date">Start Date</label>
					<input type="date" id="start-date" class="date-input" />
				</div>
				<div class="date-input-wrap">
					<label class="date-label" for="end-date">End Date</label>
					<input type="date" id="end-date" class="date-input" />
				</div>
			</div>
			<button type="button" class="date-calculate" id="calculate-btn">
				Calculate
			</button>
		</div>

		<!-- RESULTS -->
		<div class="date-results" id="date-results" style="display:none">
			<div class="date-direction-card" id="date-direction">
				<span class="date-direction-icon" id="direction-icon">⏭️</span>
				<span class="date-direction-text" id="direction-text"></span>
			</div>

			<div class="date-main-card">
				<div class="date-main-num" id="total-days">0</div>
				<div class="date-main-label">days between dates</div>
				<div class="date-exact" id="date-exact">0 years, 0 months, 0 days</div>
			</div>

			<div class="date-grid">
				<div class="date-stat-card">
					<div class="date-stat-num" id="total-weeks">0</div>
					<div class="date-stat-label">Total weeks</div>
				</div>
				<div class="date-stat-card">
					<div class="date-stat-num" id="total-hours">0</div>
					<div class="date-stat-label">Total hours</div>
				</div>
				<div class="date-stat-card">
					<div class="date-stat-num" id="total-months">0</div>
					<div class="date-stat-label">Total months</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
		<section class="date-how">
			<h2 class="date-section-title">How does a date calculator work?</h2>
			<div class="date-how-card">
				<p>
					A date calculator finds the difference between two dates by counting
					the total number of days between them. It converts both dates to a
					common reference point — typically midnight on each day — and measures
					the span in days. The result is a single number representing how many
					full calendar days separate the start date from the end date.
				</p>
				<p>
					Months and years make this more complex than simple subtraction.
					Months have different lengths — February has 28 or 29 days while
					January has 31 — so the number of days between two dates depends on
					which months fall in between. Leap years add an extra day every four
					years, giving those years 366 days instead of 365. A calculator must
					account for every varying month length and leap day to return an
					accurate total.
				</p>
				<p>
					Clockr breaks the total down into years, months, weeks, days, and
					hours for a complete picture. Alongside the raw day count, you see
					how the gap translates into full years and remaining months and days,
					plus the equivalent number of weeks and hours. This makes it easy to
					understand a date span at a glance — whether you need a precise day
					count or a more intuitive breakdown.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- FAQ -->
		<section class="date-faq">
			<h2 class="date-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="date-faq-list">
				<details class="date-faq-item">
					<summary class="date-faq-question"
						>How do I calculate the number of days between two dates?</summary
					>
					<div class="date-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Enter your start date and end date into Clockr's date calculator
							above and click Calculate. The tool counts every calendar day
							between the two dates, automatically handling varying month lengths
							and leap years. The result shows the total days plus a breakdown
							into years, months, and days for a fuller picture.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="date-faq-item">
					<summary class="date-faq-question"
						>How many days are in a year?</summary
					>
					<div class="date-faq-answer">
						<p>
							A standard year has 365 days. A leap year has 366 days, with the
							extra day falling on 29 February. Leap years occur every four
							years, except for century years not divisible by 400 — so 2000
							was a leap year but 1900 was not. Over any four-year period, the
							average is 365.25 days per year.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="date-faq-item">
					<summary class="date-faq-question"
						>What is the difference between calendar days and business days?</summary
					>
					<div class="date-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Calendar days include every day of the week — weekends and
							holidays included. Business days (or working days) count only
							weekdays, typically Monday through Friday, and often exclude
							public holidays. A gap of 14 calendar days is only 10 business
							days. Clockr's date calculator measures calendar days; for
							working-day counts, use the Business Days Calculator.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="date-faq-item">
					<summary class="date-faq-question"
						>How do I add days to a date?</summary
					>
					<div class="date-faq-answer">
						<p>
							To add days to a date, start with your base date and count forward
							on a calendar, rolling over at each month boundary. For example,
							adding 30 days to 15 January gives 14 February in a normal year
							or 15 February in a leap year. You can also use Clockr in reverse
							— set your start date and adjust the end date until the day count
							matches the number you want to add.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="date-faq-item">
					<summary class="date-faq-question"
						>How many weeks are in a year?</summary
					>
					<div class="date-faq-answer">
						<p>
							A year contains 52 full weeks plus one or two extra days. In a
							365-day year, 365 ÷ 7 equals 52 weeks and 1 day; in a leap year,
							366 ÷ 7 equals 52 weeks and 2 days. That is why a date like your
							birthday falls on the next weekday each year — or two weekdays
							later after a leap year.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="date-faq-item">
					<summary class="date-faq-question"
						>What is the longest possible gap between two dates in history?</summary
					>
					<div class="date-faq-answer">
						<p>
							In theory, the longest gap is bounded only by how far back and
							forward you can measure. From the earliest known written records
							(around 3200 BCE) to centuries into the future, the span runs into
							millions of days. In everyday use, people measure gaps from
							historic events — the moon landing, the millennium, ancient
							civilisations — to today or a future date. Clockr can calculate
							the days between any two dates your browser supports.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="date-faq-item">
					<summary class="date-faq-question"
						>How do I calculate how many days until an event?</summary
					>
					<div class="date-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Set today's date as the start date and your event date as the end
							date, then click Calculate. The total days result tells you
							exactly how long until the event. For popular occasions, use the
							preset buttons in the "Common date questions" section below —
							they auto-fill dates for Christmas, New Year, Halloween, and more.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="date-faq-item">
					<summary class="date-faq-question"
						>Why do leap years exist?</summary
					>
					<div class="date-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Earth takes roughly 365.25 days to orbit the sun, not exactly
							365. Without leap years, our calendar would drift by about one
							day every four years, and seasons would gradually shift into the
							wrong months. Adding 29 February every four years — with
							century-year exceptions — keeps the calendar aligned with the
							solar year and the changing seasons.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- COMMON QUESTIONS -->
		<div class="date-examples">
			<h3 class="date-examples-title">Common date questions</h3>
			<div class="date-examples-grid">
				<button type="button" class="date-example-btn" data-preset="christmas">
					🎄 Days until Christmas
				</button>
				<button type="button" class="date-example-btn" data-preset="new-year">
					🎆 Days until New Year
				</button>
				<button type="button" class="date-example-btn" data-preset="millennium">
					🌍 Days since the millennium
				</button>
				<button type="button" class="date-example-btn" data-preset="halloween">
					🎃 Days until Halloween
				</button>
				<button type="button" class="date-example-btn" data-preset="valentines">
					💝 Days until Valentine's Day
				</button>
				<button type="button" class="date-example-btn" data-preset="moon-landing">
					🌙 Days since the moon landing
				</button>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- RELATED TOOLS -->
		<div class="date-related">
			<h3 class="date-related-title">You might also like</h3>
			<div class="date-related-grid">
				<a href="/age-calculator" class="date-related-card">🎂 Age Calculator</a>
				<a href="/birthday-countdown" class="date-related-card"
					>🎈 Birthday Countdown</a
				>
				<a href="/how-many-seconds-alive" class="date-related-card"
					>⚡ 1 Billion Seconds</a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

